sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Route as RayCluster Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (service-ca)
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP

    User->>Router: GET /ray-dashboard<br/>HTTPS
    Router->>Route: Forward (reencrypt)<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Route->>OAuth: HTTPS<br/>service-ca cert
    OAuth->>OAuthServer: Validate user<br/>OAuth flow
    OAuthServer-->>OAuth: User authenticated<br/>Session token
    OAuth->>Dashboard: Forward request<br/>localhost HTTP
    Dashboard-->>OAuth: Dashboard response
    OAuth-->>Route: HTTPS response
    Route-->>Router: Encrypted response
    Router-->>User: Dashboard UI

    Note over User,Dashboard: Flow 1: Ray Dashboard Access (OpenShift)

    participant Client as Ray Client Pod
    participant RayService as Ray Client Service<br/>10001/TCP
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>10001/TCP mTLS

    Client->>RayService: Ray API request<br/>mTLS (client cert)
    RayService->>RayHead: Forward request<br/>mTLS validated
    RayHead-->>RayService: Ray response
    RayService-->>Client: Response

    Note over Client,RayHead: Flow 3: Ray Client Connection (mTLS)

    participant UserCI as User/CI
    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Webhook as CodeFlare Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as CodeFlare Controller
    participant K8sAPI as K8s API

    UserCI->>APIServer: Create RayCluster CR<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>User credentials
    APIServer->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Validated CR
    APIServer->>Controller: Watch notification<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Resources<br/>Services, Routes, NetworkPolicies<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over UserCI,K8sAPI: Flow 2: RayCluster Creation

    participant SDK as User/SDK
    participant AWWebhook as AppWrapper Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AWController as AppWrapper Controller
    participant KueueAPI as Kueue API

    SDK->>APIServer: Create AppWrapper CR<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    APIServer->>AWWebhook: Validate<br/>mTLS
    AWWebhook-->>APIServer: Validated
    APIServer->>AWController: Watch notification<br/>ServiceAccount token
    AWController->>KueueAPI: Create Workload CR<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    KueueAPI-->>AWController: Queue position
    AWController->>K8sAPI: Create wrapped resources<br/>when admitted

    Note over SDK,K8sAPI: Flow 4: AppWrapper with Kueue

    participant Prom as Prometheus
    participant SvcMonitor as ServiceMonitor
    participant MetricsSvc as Metrics Service<br/>8080/TCP
    participant Operator as Operator Pod<br/>8080/TCP

    Prom->>SvcMonitor: Discover targets
    Prom->>MetricsSvc: Scrape metrics<br/>HTTPS (service-ca on OpenShift)<br/>Bearer token
    MetricsSvc->>Operator: Forward to pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Operator-->>MetricsSvc: Prometheus metrics
    MetricsSvc-->>Prom: Metrics data

    Note over Prom,Operator: Flow 5: Metrics Collection
